      <h1 class='title'>1914&#x2013;1919</h1>
    </div>
    <div class='house-of-lords-report' id='content'>
      
      <cite class='section'> Deb 30 July 1931 vol 81 c1307</cite>
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_1307' title='Col. 1307 &mdash;  Deb 30 July 1931 vol 81 c1307' name='column_1307' href='#column_1307' rel='bookmark'>1307</a>
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0081P0-03843'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0081P0_19310730_HOLR2_1' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        should be placed on the pedestal of the statue, and that those words should be repeated on the first tablet at the head of the list of names. I should like to take this opportunity of recording the appreciation of the Committee for the help which they have received from the officials of His Majesty's Office of Works in connection with several matters which have arisen in the course of their deliberations. I should add that formal sanction has been given by the Lord Great Chamberlain, so that in view of the progress which I have been able to describe, I trust that nothing will now arise to prevent the completion and erection of the Memorial by the end of the present year.
      </p>
